                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>An agreement between the United States and Portugal granting American aircraft
                    the right to continue using transit facilities in the Azores was effected by an
                    exchange of notes signed at Lisbon February 2, 1948; operative retroactively to
                    December 2, 1947. For text of Agreement, see Department of State Treaties and
                    Other International Acts Series (<gloss target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss>) No.
                    2351; United States Treaties and Other International Agreements (UST), volume 2
                    (pt. 2), page 2266.</p>
            </div>
